  "prompt": "Do some people without mental illnesses see therapists?",
  "response": "Yes, many people without diagnosed mental illnesses see therapists. Therapy can be beneficial for a wide range of reasons beyond mental illness, including stress management, personal development, relationship issues, career guidance, and coping with life transitions. It can also be a proactive way to maintain mental well-being, improve communication skills, and enhance overall quality of life. Therapy provides a safe space for individuals to explore their thoughts, emotions, and behaviors, and to develop strategies for handling various challenges more effectively.",
